The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Ruia scripts Falcon success story

 A STAFF REPORTER

 Calcutta, June 2: After coming into the folds of the Ruia group, Falcon Tyres has registered close to 300 per cent growth in earnings and announced its highest ever dividend of 25 per cent, or Rs 2.50 per share, for 2005-06. 

 Last fiscal, the company reported a net profit of Rs 3.63 crore against Rs 92 lakh in 2004-05. 

 Total turnover in the reporting year stood at Rs 255.63 crore against Rs 219.86 crore in the previous year. 

 In the fourth quarter of fiscal 2006, Falcon posted a net profit of Rs 1.39 crore against Rs 12.61 lakh in the same period previous fiscal.

 The Ruia Group took over Falcon Tyres in December 2005 along with two other companies, Dunlop India Ltd and India Tyres amp; Rubber, from the Chhabria-controlled Jumbo Group.

 Taking stock of the companys numbers today, chairman Pawan Kumar Ruia said, The jump in profit is the result of de-bottlenecking the production capacity of Falcon.

 The company has embarked on a Rs 60-crore expansion plan. The expansion is expected to be completed this fiscal. 

 We are looking at Sumitomo for the latest technology in the two-wheeler and three-wheeler tyre segments, Ruia added.

 Falcon manufactures and markets a wide range of two and three-wheeler tyres. 




